sql:
SELECT group_name, group_size
FROM student_groups
WHERE group_size > (SELECT AVG(group_size) FROM student_groups);

SELECT group_name
FROM student_groups
WHERE group_size > 100;

external_knowledge:
- 'English learners' refers to students who are in the process of learning English as a new language;
- The query focuses on those with a 'progress_level' of 'English', indicating they are part of the English learning program;
- 'Total hours of instruction' measures the cumulative time spent on English learning activities;
- 'Total days absent' indicates how many days of classes were missed by the group as a whole.

sql:
SELECT SUM(group_size)
FROM student_groups
WHERE created_date < '2022-01-01';

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM policy_changes 
WHERE responsible_department = 'Counseling Department';

SELECT AVG(average_score) AS Average_Score
FROM student_performance
WHERE metric_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_absenteeism_records, AVG(absenteeism_rate) AS average_absenteeism_rate
FROM absenteeism_records
WHERE record_date BETWEEN '2023-01-01' AND '2023-05-01';

external_knowledge:
- "Rising stars" metaphorically refers to individuals who have shown excellent performance;
- "Asian community" represents the group with the name 'Asian';
- "Performance metrics they have shone in" relates to the metrics where their performance level is marked as 'Yes'.

sql:
SELECT sg.group_name, sp.performance_level
FROM student_groups sg
JOIN student_performance sp ON sg.group_id = sp.group_id;

SELECT policy_name, responsible_department
FROM policy_changes
WHERE implementation_date > '2020-01-01';

external_knowledge:
- Larger study groups refer to groups having 50 or more students;
- Enhancing English reading skills specifically targets the 'English Reading Performance' metric;
- Surpassed the expected target means the average score is higher than the target value set for the metric.

'excelled the most' refers to having the highest average score; 'in English reading' refers to the metric 'English Reading Performance'.;
The metric name 'English Reading Performance' is a key performance indicator used to assess the proficiency of students in reading English.;
